    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package for submission despite all seven assessed factors showing achieved levels below required levels and six factors flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps. Acceptance was granted on the basis that the Monte Carlo UQ bounds were judged conservative and the 8.3 % MAPE was considered acceptable pending re-validation. NOTE: This acceptance is undermined by W-AR-04 — the ValidationResult evidence (hemolysis-cfd-vs-invitro-2024 and hemolysis-mesh-sensitivity-2024) was generated by ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-15-build-2024q3-2 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2), which predates the UofA currentModelVersion 2026-q1-build-7 by over 18 months and does not reflect the turbulence-model recalibration introduced in the 2026 Q1 build. The supporting validation evidence no longer applies to the model of record.",
